@201  = ~psionicist~
@202  = ~Psionicist~
@203  = ~PSIONICIST: the Psionicist is someone who (mostly) turns away from larcenous pursuits, and focuses on education and meditation to fully harness the power of the mind and the body. Psionicists are generally very well-educated and very healthy, treating their body as a temple. Through study and discipline, they can learn to use psychic abilities from any psionic discipline.

Abilities:
- Begins with access to the first power in all five psionic disciplines: Mind Thrust, Project Force, Static Discharge, Adrenaline Rush, and Object Reading. The Psionicist can proceed to learn an additional power with each new level of experience, from any psionic discipline.
- Gains one extra hit point on every even level, up to level 20.

Restrictions:
- May only distribute 12 skill points per level into thief skills.
- May not Pick Pockets or Set Traps.
- May not be Chaotic.
~
@301  = ~soulblade~
@302  = ~Soulblade~
@303  = ~SOULBLADE: this warrior uses meditation to harness psychic powers in order to enhance <PRO_HISHER> martial abilities. Often training with Psionicists or Psyphers, the Soulblade can use a select few psionic abilities, generally those which fortify <PRO_HISHER> body or mind against attacks.

Abilities:
- Begins with access to the first power in all five psionic disciplines: Mind Thrust, Project Force, Static Discharge, Adrenaline Rush, and Object Reading. The Soulblade can proceed to learn an additional power at every odd level of experience, from any psionic discipline.

Restrictions:
- Gains hit dice as a priest (d8) instead of a warrior.
- Limited to medium armors.
- Limited to Mastery (+++) with melee weapons.
- Limited to Proficiency (+) with ranged weapons.
- May not be Chaotic.
~
@401  = ~psypher~
@402  = ~Psypher~
@403  = ~PSYPHER: the Psypher is ... Through study and discipline, they can learn to use psychic abilities from any psionic discipline.

Abilities:
- Begins with access to the first power in all five psionic disciplines: Mind Thrust, Project Force, Static Discharge, Adrenaline rush, and Insightful Strike. The Psypher can proceed to learn an additional power with each new level of experience, from any psionic discipline.
- Gains one extra hit point on every even level, up to level 20.

Restrictions:
- May not be Chaotic.
- Does not become innately resistant to magic.
- Cannot Lay On Hands or use any other traditional Monk abilities.
~
