@2011  = ~Project Force~
@2012  = ~Project Force: this ability blasts a target with powerful but unfocused telekinetic energy, causing 2d3 stunning damage and, upon a failed saving throw, knocking the target back 5 feet. Additionally, this ability has a 50% chance to break open locks. At 6th level the damage is 2d4 and the save is rolled with a -1 penalty; at 12th level the damage is 2d6 and the save is rolled with a -2 penalty.

The cost is 4 hit points.~
@2014  = ~Contingency: activate Project Force at attacker, when hit~
@2031  = ~Immobilize~
@2032  = ~Immobilize: the target of this power is held frozen in place, unable to move or act, upon a failed saving throw. On the second round and each round thereafter, up to ten rounds, an immobilized target may attempt another save to escape the effect. Even if a save is made, the target is very briefly Slowed while fighting off the telekinetic control. At levels 6 and 12, the target's saving throw is rolled with a -1 and -2 penalty, respectively.

The cost is 6 hit points.~
@2041  = ~Inertial Barrier~
@2042  = ~Inertial Barrier: this ability creates a movable barrier inches from the psion's skin, which has several protective effects: it provides a +2 bonus to AC and 40% damage resistance against crushing and missile attacks; a +1 AC bonus and 20% damage resistance against slashing attacks; 25% resistance to fire, acid, and magic damage; and immunity to the Magic Missile spell.

The cost to maintain the Barrier is 6 hit points.~
@2043  = ~Cancel Inertial Barrier~
@2051  = ~Psychic Knife~
@2052  = ~Psychic Knife: the psion can focus telekinetic energy into a razor-sharp blade emanating from <PRO_HISHER> hand. This force can be wielded like a sword, as if the rogue had Mastery (+++) in its use, doing 1d4 slashing damage and 1d4 magic damage.  At 12th level, the blade is wielded as if with Grandmastery.

The cost to maintain the Psychic Knife is 6 hit points.~
@2053  = ~Cancel Psychic Knife~
@2071  = ~Repulsion~
@2072  = ~Repulsion: this ability creates an unfocused surge of telekinetic force which throws anyone nearby away from the psion (except allies, who can be shielded from the effect), unless they make a saving throw vs. Breath. While the ability is maintained, this surge of force builds and is released once per 3 seconds.  

The cost to maintain the repulsion effect is 9 hit points.~
@2073  = ~Cancel Repulsion~
@2081  = ~Free Action~
@2082  = ~Free Action: this ability allows the psion to break free of any bonds; and to avoid being caught or held by any effect that affects <PRO_HISHER> mobility. Such spells or events will fail to affect the psion as long as this ability is maintained.

The cost to maintain free Action is 9 hit points.~
@2083  = ~Cancel Free Action~
@2084  = ~Contingency: activate Free Action when helpless~
@2091  = ~Mass Immobilize~
@2092  = ~Mass Immobilize: all enemies within 20' of the psion are held frozen in place, unable to move or act, upon a failed saving throw. On the second round and each round thereafter, up to ten rounds, each immobilized target may attempt another save to escape the effect. Even if a save is made, the target is very briefly Slowed while fighting off the telekinetic control. At levels 6 and 12, the target's saving throw is rolled with a -1 and -2 penalty, respectively.

The cost is 9 hit points.~
@2094  = ~Contingency: activate Mass Immobilize at 50% hit points~
@2111  = ~Seismic Vibration~
@2112  = ~Seismic Vibration: this ability causes a strong tremor to affect the ground nearby. All enemies in the vicinity take damage over the course of three rounds, and must make a saving throw or fall down in the first round.

Using this ability increases the psion's fatigue and causes a 20-point temporary reduction in <PRO_HISHER> max hit points.~
